JITLIFE Privacy Policy
Important Notice

Your trust is of utmost importance to us. We fully recognize the significance of your personal information and are committed to protecting it in compliance with applicable laws and regulations through appropriate security measures. Accordingly, Chengdu Oriental Zhixiang Technology Co., Ltd. (hereinafter referred to as "JITLIFE" or "we") has formulated this JITLIFE Privacy Policy (hereinafter referred to as "this Policy") and hereby informs you as follows:

Please note: This Policy applies only to JITLIFE products and services, not to services provided by third parties or to JITLIFE products/services that have separate privacy policies.

Before using any JITLIFE product or service, please read this Policy carefully and ensure you fully understand and agree to its terms. If you have questions, suggestions, or concerns, please contact us via the channels provided by JITLIFE.

This Policy is developed and implemented based on the following principles:

Principle of Consistency of Rights and Responsibilities

Purpose Limitation

Explicit Consent

Data Minimization

Security Assurance

User Participation

Transparency

Part I: Definitions
JITLIFE: Refers to the JITLIFE mobile client (including but not limited to mini-programs, WeChat official accounts, etc.).

JITLIFE Service Provider: Chengdu Oriental Zhixiang Technology Co., Ltd., the provider of JITLIFE mobile client and software services, registered at *9th Floor, Building 3, No. 200, Tianfu Fifth Street, Hi-Tech Zone (West), Chengdu, China (Sichuan) Pilot Free Trade Zone*.

Affiliates: Companies directly or indirectly controlled by or affiliated with JITLIFE.

Personal Information: Any information recorded electronically or otherwise that can identify or reflect the activities of a specific natural person, either alone or in combination with other information.

Sensitive Personal Information: Includes ID numbers, biometric data, bank account details, financial information, location trajectories, transaction records, and information of children under 14 (such data will be bolded, underlined, or otherwise highlighted in this Policy).

Personal Information Deletion: The act of removing personal information from operational systems to render it irretrievable or inaccessible.

Unless otherwise specified, terms in this Policy align with those defined in the JITLIFE Service Agreement.

