1. How We Collect and Use Your Information
We collect and use your personal information in the following scenarios:

(1) Essential Information for Core Services
To provide basic functionalities (e.g., account registration), you must authorize us to collect necessary information. Without this, you cannot use our services.

(2) Optional Information for Enhanced Services
For additional features (e.g., personalized recommendations), you may choose to authorize data collection. Refusal will not affect core services.

(3) Indirect Collection

During registration/use, we may obtain information from third parties (with your consent) to prevent fraud or illegal activities.

When using third-party accounts (e.g., WeChat) to log in, we may bind your account to JITLIFE after obtaining shared details (nickname, avatar, region, gender).

Key Notes:

Services vary by user, so data collection scope and purposes may differ.

We may update data practices for new features, notifying you via updates, pop-ups, etc.

Data is stored within China. Cross-border transfers require your explicit consent.

Refusing core data collection may disable essential services.

Specific Use Cases:

Account Registration

Mobile number, password, and verification code are required.

Optional: Nickname, avatar, gender, and birthday.

WeChat login: We obtain your WeChat nickname, avatar, region, and gender (with consent).

Bluetooth Search, Connection, and Data Transmission

Required for device pairing and functionality.

Auto-Start Permissions

For full app functionality (e.g., background location access to search Bluetooth devices).

You may disable location permissions in device settings.

Additional Rules:

If you provide others’ personal information, ensure you have legal authorization.

Any new uses of collected data will require prior consent.

Exceptions to Consent:
We may process your information without consent in cases involving:

National/Public Security

Crime Investigation/Judicial Proceedings

Protection of Life/Property

Publicly Available Information

Legal Reporting or Research

2. Use of Cookies and Similar Technologies
(1) Cookies
To optimize website functionality, we may store cookies on your device. You can adjust browser settings to reject cookies, but this may affect site accessibility.

(2) Similar Technologies

Web Beacons/Pixel Tags: Track email opens or page interactions.

ETags: Improve server efficiency (disable via browser cache clearing).

3. Sharing, Transfer, and Disclosure of Your Information
(1) Sharing
We may share data under these circumstances:

Legal requirements

With your explicit consent

For transactions (e.g., sharing order details with suppliers)

With affiliates or authorized partners (e.g., advertisers, analytics providers, logistics vendors)

(2) Transfer
Data may be transferred during mergers, acquisitions, or bankruptcy, provided the recipient adheres to this Policy.

(3) Disclosure
We may disclose your information:

With your consent

To address legal violations or protect user safety

Exceptions to Consent:
No consent is required for sharing/transfer/disclosure in cases of national security, public interest, or legal obligations.

4. How We Protect Your Information
Security Measures: Encryption, access controls, SSL, HTTPS, employee training.

Data Retention: Retained only as necessary (e.g., 3 years for e-commerce transactions under Chinese law).

Incident Response: Prompt notification of breaches and remediation steps.

5. Your Rights
You may:

Access, correct, or delete your information

Withdraw consent or restrict automated decisions

Request data portability

Lodge complaints

Submit requests via contact details below. We respond within 15 business days.

Exceptions: We may refuse requests involving national security, legal investigations, or trade secrets.

6. Minors’ Information
Minors must obtain parental/guardian consent before using our services. We protect minors’ data per applicable laws.

7. Cross-Border Data Transfers
Data is stored in China unless:

Required by law

With your explicit consent

For cross-border transactions

8. Policy Updates
We will notify you of significant changes (e.g., via in-app notices). Major updates include:

Changes to data purposes or types

Ownership transfers

New sharing/disclosure practices

